    <!--
      Narrative Plan:
      The infographic tells a story starting from a high-level overview (Overall Performance), then drills down into specific performance dimensions (Monthly, Channel, Location, etc.). Each section presents data visually and is accompanied by key insights. The story concludes with specific, actionable recommendations for future campaigns, focusing on Landing Page optimization and strategic budget allocation.

      Visualization Choices (Justification, NO SVG/Mermaid):
      - Overall Performance: Goal: Inform/Compare. Big Number Cards (HTML/CSS) for impact. Grouped Bar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) to clearly compare Plan vs. Actual.
      - Monthly Performance: Goal: Change. Combination Bar/Line Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) is ideal for showing the relationship between a volume metric (Budget) and rate metrics (costs, percentages) over time.
      - Channel Performance: Goal: Compare. Combination Bar/Line Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) effectively compares budget allocation against multiple performance KPIs for a few categories.
      - Location Performance: Goal: Compare/Organize. An Ordered Horizontal Bar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) is excellent for ranking locations by performance (% Cost/Disbursement) and is easy to read.
      - Landing Page Performance: Goal: Compare. A Grouped Bar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) provides a direct, easy-to-understand comparison between two competing entities on multiple metrics.
      - Top Keyword Groups: Goal: Organize/Rank. An Ordered Horizontal Bar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) clearly visualizes the top-performing keyword groups, making it easy to see the ranking.
      - Audience Performance: Goal: Compare. A Polar Area Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) offers visual variety while still effectively comparing the magnitude of performance (% Cost/Disbursement) across different audience segments.
      - Banner Performance: Goal: Compare. A Combination Bar/Line Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) is used to show multiple KPIs (costs as bars, final efficiency as a line) for a clear A/B comparison.
      - LP Optimization: Goal: Organize/Inform. A diagram built with structured HTML/CSS and Tailwind is used to present a process flow and comparative concepts, avoiding SVG/Mermaid.
      - Key Learnings/Recommendations: Goal: Inform/Organize. Styled lists using HTML/CSS provide a clear, scannable summary of key takeaways and actions.

      Confirmation: NEITHER Mermaid JS NOR SVG were used in this output. All charts are rendered on Canvas by Chart.js. All diagrams are built with HTML/CSS.
    -->
