        <!-- Slide 1: Overall Performance -->
        <section id="overall" class="section-card">
            <h2 class="text-center">Overall Campaign Performance</h2>
            <div class="text-center mb-10">
                <h3>A strategic focus on quality over quantity led to exceptional results in final-funnel metrics.</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8 text-center">
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 font-light">Leads vs. Plan</p>
                    <p class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-2">99%</p>
                    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Slightly below plan, reflecting a focus on quality.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card kpi-card-green">
                    <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 font-light">Qualified Leads vs. Plan</p>
                    <p class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-2">108%</p>
                     <p class="text-sm text-green-600 font-semibold mt-2">▲ 8% Above Target</p>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card kpi-card-green">
                    <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 font-light">Disbursement vs. Plan</p>
                    <p class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-2">136%</p>
                     <p class="text-sm text-green-600 font-semibold mt-2">▲ 36% Above Target</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-container h-[50vh]">
                <canvas id="overallChart"></canvas>
            </div>
            <div class="analysis-text mx-auto">
                <p><strong>Analysis:</strong> The campaign successfully exceeded its primary goals for Disbursement (+36%) and Qualified Leads (+8%). The total number of leads was slightly below target (99%), which reflects a deliberate strategy to focus on higher-quality audience segments. This approach sacrificed some top-of-funnel volume to maximize final conversions, proven by a Cost/Disbursement ratio that was 26% better than planned.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 2: Monthly Performance -->
        <section id="monthly" class="section-card">
            <h2 class="text-center">Monthly Performance</h2>
            <div class="chart-container h-[50vh]">
                <canvas id="monthlyChart"></canvas>
            </div>
            <div class="analysis-text mx-auto">
                <p><strong>Analysis:</strong> Performance varied significantly by month. <strong>February</strong> was the most efficient month with the lowest Cost/Disbursement (13.23%), likely due to a smaller, more easily optimized budget. <strong>April</strong> also performed well (22.66%) despite a large budget, driven by the focus on the Simple Landing Page. <strong>May</strong> had the highest Cost/Disbursement (33.60%) due to several factors: budget fluctuations, frequent changes between landing pages, and the fact that disbursement data for May was not yet fully recorded as of early June.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 3: Channel Performance -->
        <section id="channels" class="section-card">
            <h2 class="text-center">Channel Performance</h2>
            <div class="chart-container h-[50vh]">
                <canvas id="channelChart"></canvas>
            </div>
             <div class="analysis-text mx-auto">
                <p><strong>Analysis:</strong> <strong>SEM</strong> was the most effective channel for driving final conversions, achieving the lowest Cost/Disbursement (19%) despite having the largest budget. While <strong>GPM</strong> delivered the cheapest leads (lowest CPL & CPQL), its high Cost/Disbursement (33%) indicates that these leads were of lower quality and harder to convert into actual loans.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 4: Location Performance -->
        <section id="locations" class="section-card">
             <h2 class="text-center">Location Performance</h2>
             <div class="chart-container h-[50vh]">
                <canvas id="locationChart"></canvas>
            </div>
            <div class="analysis-text mx-auto">
                <p><strong>Analysis:</strong> The **Central** and **Mekong** regions were the clear winners, boasting an exceptionally low Cost/Disbursement of only 14%. This is significantly more efficient than the South (32%) and especially the North (45%), which was the most expensive region despite receiving the second-largest budget allocation.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 5: Landing Page Performance -->
        <section id="landingpages" class="section-card">
            <h2 class="text-center">Landing Page Performance</h2>
            <div class="chart-container h-[50vh]">
                <canvas id="lpChart"></canvas>
            </div>
             <div class="analysis-text mx-auto">
                <p><strong>Analysis:</strong> Performance was heavily influenced by budget and timing. At first glance, the `Normal LP` appears superior with a 15% Cost/Disbursement. However, this was largely achieved in Jan/Feb with smaller budgets. Conversely, the `Simple LP` was used during high-budget months, especially May, where its performance was impacted by incomplete disbursement data. The `Simple LP` remains a highly effective tool for generating low-cost leads (CPL/CPQL) at scale.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Slide 6: Keyword Performance -->
        <section id="keywords" class="section-card">
             <h2 class="text-center">Top Keyword Groups</h2>
             <div class="chart-container h-[60vh]">
                <canvas id="keywordChart"></canvas>
            </div>
             <div class="analysis-text mx-auto">
                <p><strong>Analysis:</strong> Out of 25 keyword groups, those with clear intent demonstrated the best performance. Niche product keywords like **"Vay Bảo Hiểm Nhân Thọ" (Loan by Life Insurance)** and brand-related terms **(Lotte Finance)** were the most efficient. In contrast, indirect keywords like "buy car" or "fix house" received little budget from the system due to low relevance to the landing page content.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Slide 7: Audience Performance -->
        <section id="audience" class="section-card">
             <h2 class="text-center">Audience Performance (GPM & GDE)</h2>
            <div class="chart-container h-[50vh]">
                <canvas id="audienceChart"></canvas>
            </div>
             <div class="analysis-text mx-auto">
                <p><strong>Analysis:</strong> **Retargeting** was by far the most effective strategy, yielding the lowest Cost/Disbursement (13.73%). This proves the value of re-engaging users who have already shown interest. Further segmenting the "past performance" audience by gender **(Female)** also proved effective (22.05%). Combining the high-performance audience with a normal targeting audience diluted the quality and resulted in the poorest performance (33.69%).</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Slide 8: Banner Performance -->
        <section id="banners" class="section-card">
            <h2 class="text-center">Banner Package Performance</h2>
            <div class="chart-container h-[50vh]">
                <canvas id="bannerChart"></canvas>
            </div>
             <div class="analysis-text mx-auto">
                <p><strong>Analysis:</strong> **Pack 1** significantly outperformed Pack 2. Its creative, which combined authentic imagery of people with clear program highlights, resonated better with target audiences and drove better performance. In contrast, **Pack 2**, which relied only on promotional text, was considerably less effective, resulting in a Cost/Disbursement ratio more than double that of Pack 1.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Slide 9: LP Optimization Recommendations -->
        <section id="lp-optimization" class="section-card">
            <h2 class="text-center">Recommendation: Landing Page Optimization</h2>
